ton h. sanford, purchased two stallions five mares shipment back honolulu, although contradictory reports louisville press stated purchase horses. afterward returned cincinnati boarded another train heading west.[88][89] scheduled layover chicago, disembarked long enough breakfast answer some brief media questions train resumed route.[89] omaha, nebraska, king guest honor reception held home judge james m. woolworth. attendees friends judge's daughter, met king vacation hawaii. although kalākaua claimed exhaustion world trip, nevertheless danced whole night women guests.[90] claus mrs. spreckels joined group ogden, utah.[91] arrived california october 11.[92] part king's stay spreckels summer home aptos,[93] sightseeing trip lick observatory. guest spreckels home, sugar baron gave king two horses colt.[91] california friends king joined farewell dinner palace hotel san francisco october 22, prior sailing steamship australia back honolulu. among attending spreckels, governor perkins, california state senator paul neumann, university california president horace davis.[94][91] honolulu homecoming: october 29 – november 6 welcome arch honolulu decorated honor kalākaua's return home australia expected arrive hawaii october 31. plans kalākaua's homecoming celebration hawaii begun august, included every organized civic labor union group, well student body every school oahu. general public invited participate festivities.[95] honolulu final stages preparation october 29, australia flying kalākaua's royal flag sailed past diamond head, making way honolulu harbor.[91] alert quickly spread across oahu, battery guns began firing along waterfront diamond head port, frenzied scramble began complete decorations.[96] 281 days constant travel, hawaii's last king home. homecoming celebration went days. officials general population island crowded shoreline cheer returning monarch. speeches made english hawaiian, some people stood rooftops glimpse. floral arrangements permeated city, w