ani palace nomination form" (pdf). national register historic places. u.s. national park service. retrieved december 31, 2016. ^ kuykendall 1967, p.262; "grand masonic banquet". honolulu, hawaiian islands: pacific commercial advertiser. december 30, 1882. retrieved december 27, 2016 – via chronicling america: historic american newspapers. lib. congress. ^ "electric light". honolulu, hawaiian islands: daily bulletin. july 22, 1866. retrieved december 27, 2016 – via chronicling america: historic american newspapers. lib. congress. ^ b c kuykendall 1967, p.259 ^ "crowned! kalakaua's coronation accomplished: large unenthusiatic assemblage!". honolulu, hawaiian islands: hawaiian gazette. february 14, 1883. retrieved december 30, 2016 – via chronicling america: historic american newspapers. lib. congress. ^ harper's 1891 ^ kuykendall 1967, pp.143, 158, 189 ^ kuykendall 1967, pp.300, 312–313, 324 references armstrong, william n. (1904). around world king. new york, ny: f. a. stokes company – via hathitrust. char, tin-yuke (1976). "a hawaiian king visits hong kong, 1881". journal hong kong branch royal asiatic society. royal asiatic society hong kong branch. 16: 92–106. jstor23886747. (subscription required (help)). dias, eduardo mayon (winter 1984). "here comes "kalakana": king kalakaua's visit portugal seen portuguese press". biography. university hawai'i press. 7 (1): 74–90 – via project muse. (subscription required (help)). hansen, ron (summer 2005). "wilde omaha". prairie schooner. university nebraska press. 79 (2): 5–23 – via project muse. (subscription required (help)). harper's (january–june 1891). "king kalakaua hawaii". harper's weekly. harper's magazine co. 35: 95–96 – via hathitrust. kaeo, peter; queen emma (1976). korn, alfons l., ed. news molokai, letters peter kaeo queen emma, 1873–1876. honolulu: university press hawaii. hdl:10125/39980. isbn978-0-8248-0399-5. oclc2225064. kanahele, george s. (1999). emma: hawaii's remarkable queen. honolulu: university hawa